The intense fear among an alarming number of white people has caused violent white supremacy to increasingly overlap with mainstream conservative rhetoric.
Conservative parties see themselves facing a much more real demographic challenge than even the imagined fears of the racists they have courted.
But crucially, it also neatly aligned conservative parties with racists—and aligned their existentially pessimistic rhetoric as well.
The Republican Party (conservative parties abroad face similar trends) is now increasingly a whites-only party.
They’re simply acting on the same logic and implied rhetoric of the conservative parties they have come to dominate.